`_.assign` and `_.merge` cause problems when working with immutable data, because they modify the inputs.

``` js
let x = {a: 1, b: 2}, y = {a: 3}
_.assign(x, y) // {a: 3, b: 2}
x // {a: 3, b: 2}
```

``` js
let x = {a: 1, b: 2}, y = {a: 3}
_.update(x, y) // {a: 3, b: 2}
x // {a: 1, b: 2}
```

Dummy implementation:

``` js
